Couldn’t fault it.

reviews_data.review_text: Thanks Chiara for excellent service!

So thankful Kiki moved into the neighborhood. Wowwwww I’m blown away by their Greek food. The village salad was incredible, tzatziki, fava, & pita were lovely, cocktails were some of the best/ most creative in sea point, the halloumi was unreal, and the service + atmosphere was the cherry on top. Make a reservation bc I’m sure they’ll be busy. Can’t wait to come back again!

reviews_data.review_text:
A beautifully designed space, but the food and service were very mediocre and the food overpriced.

Fish was good but it was R425 for the main excluding sides. The chops were thin and not very well flavoured. The waitress seemed disappointed with us because we only ordered a few things to share and not very many drinks. One person at the table had celiac disease, we asked if the main courses that had arrived were safe, she said she would check with the kitchen and then she  never returned.

All in all, a lot of potential, but wouldn’t return.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Warren, thank you for your review. We're disappointed to hear that our food and service didn't meet your expectations. Regarding the pricing of our dishes, we take great pride in sourcing high-quality, fresh ingredients to ensure the best possible dining experience. The pricing reflects the premium quality of our ingredients and the care that goes into each dish.  As for our service, we take food allergies and intolerances seriously and apologise that the dietary concerns weren’t addressed adequately. We hold ourselves to high standards when accommodating our guests’ needs, including those with dietary restrictions. We are further investigating this incident to prevent it from happening again. Your feedback is invaluable to us, and we’d love the opportunity to welcome you back and provide you with an exceptional experience from start to end.

reviews_data.review_text:
My girlfriend and I share a deep love for Greek food—it’s our go-to cuisine when we’re unsure what to eat, whether we’re making it at home, grabbing a quick gyro, or enjoying a meze-style feast.

So, when we heard about the opening of Kiki, a new Greek restaurant, we didn’t walk—we ran!

The interior is beautifully designed—simple yet sophisticated—and immediately set the tone for a great evening.

We started with cocktails: an espresso martini for her and a classic margarita for me. Both were fantastic. While we sipped, we were served some bread with Greek olive oil, herbs, and some of the tastiest olives I’ve had in a long time. A delightful way to begin!

The menu was so tempting that we quickly realized we’d need to come back to try everything. For starters, we went with the fire flatbread and spicy feta dip. Both were solid, though the dip could have used a bit more heat.

Kiki operates with two dinner seatings, and unfortunately, the first seating had polished off all the halloumi—so we’ll definitely be returning for that!

We ordered a second round of cocktails—an Aperol spritz and a Paloma—before moving on to the beef meatballs and dolmades. The meatballs could have benefited from a touch more salt and herbs for freshness, but the dolmades were perfect. My girlfriend made sure to snag most of those!

Next up, we had the baby squid in mermaid sauce, crispy chicken thighs with toum, and the crispy potatoes. The chicken thighs were exceptionally crispy and paired beautifully with the toum, which was outstanding. The pickles on the plate were a bit too acidic for my taste, but that’s a personal preference.

Overall, we had a fantastic evening. The food, the cocktails, and the atmosphere all made for a memorable experience. Kiki has officially been added to our go-to restaurant rotation. Be sure to book in advance—it’s worth it!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Jarred, we are on cloud nine and it is all because of your wonderful review! We are ecstatic that you enjoyed your experience at our establishment and honoured to be on your list of rotation restaurants. We are excited to welcome you back - don't let us wait too long.

reviews_data.review_text:
Terrible food … clearly the chef’s never been in Greece.

We tried two appetizers and two mains.

The meat was dry, the pasta with crab had minimal quantity of crab and no distinctive taste.

The halloumi was made in the wrongest possible way , and the other appetizer was okeyish.

Such a pity…. The place is gorgeous, but unfortunately looks like I’ve found the only place in Cape Town where the food tastes bad.

Looks as if the chef heard about Greece , read online recipes and imagined how the food would taste .. the result is weird, or simply not tasty, and neither well prepared.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Marieta, thank you for your review. We’re sorry to hear that your experience didn’t fully meet your expectations, especially as our team did their utmost to make your visit enjoyable. We sincerely appreciate your kind words about the ambience and are grateful you chose to dine with us. Although this visit wasn’t quite what you’d hoped for, we do hope you’ll consider joining us again to explore more of what our menu has to offer.

It is the perfect atmosphere to visit and enjoy each other's company. The staff are on the ball, extremely efficient,  friendly, and ready to offer great menu options. It is definitely the kind of restaurant that will become a firm favourite.  Thank you for a brilliant dining experience.
